          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1CANTMF"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment carried out using the",
                "DRAGON recoil separator at TRIUMF, Vancouver"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Helium-filled DRAGON windowless gas target with",
                "effective length of (12.3+-0.1) cm and He pressure",
                "between 4.92 and 7.9 torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For mass and momentum selection an",
                "electromagnetic mass separator was used, which",
                "consists of two magnetic (M) and two electric dipoles",
                " (E) in a MEME configuration."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Prompt gamma rays were detected using an array",
                "of 30 BGO scintillators with phototubes covering",
                "covering 89-92% of the 4Pi solid angle. It was used",
                "also fore tagging of the associated recoil particles",
                "for additional background reduction in the focal",
                "plane detectors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Focal plane detector consisting of",
                "microchannel plate and a double-sided silicon-strip",
                "detector. The microchannel plate provided the",
                "starting timing sig nalfor a local time-of-flight. In",
                "the Si strip detector the recoils are stopped, their",
                "kinetic energy and position are measured, and the",
                "stopping timing signal is recorded."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Beams of 7Be+ were produced using the ISOL technique",
                "by bombarding thick ZrC and graphite targets with 55",
                "muA 500 MeV protons from the TRIUMF cyclotron. 7Li",
                "and 7Be were extracted from the target through a",
                "high-resolution mass separator, and the beryllium",
                "ionization was enhanced using the TRIUMF Resonant",
                "Ionization Laser Ion Source. After the ion source,",
                "the beam was transported through the ISAC",
                "high-resolution mass separator and then accelerated",
                "through the ISAC-I radio frequency quadrupole and",
                "drift-tube linac to final energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
